1. Adding virtual env:
a) virtual environment
file-> settings->project:<> -> python Interpreter ->add interpreter -> virtual environment (new)
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qcpLYKCNYNM&ab_channel=JorgosAndreadis
(has pytest also)

b) System interpreter: To have all the packages installed in your system
(could see this from cmd prompt using: pip list command)
file-> settings->project:<> -> python Interpreter ->add interpreter -> System interpreter (new)
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d_viFr3w4g8&ab_channel=MohanKumartech

2. Reference: 
https://beam.apache.org/documentation/transforms/python/aggregation/cogroupbykey/
https://beam.apache.org/get-started/quickstart-py/

3. Activate virtual env and Installing packages
python -m venv /path/to/directory
C:\Users\jeeva\PycharmProjects\pythonProject\venv\Scripts\activate.bat

4. Pypi.org: has the s/w package to install
a) To install: file-> settings->project:<> -> python Interpreter -> + -> search the package and install. 

b) or 
pip install apache_beam
pip install apache_beam[gcp]
pip install google-cloud-storage

. /path/to/directory/bin/activate